{"id": 120775075, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/jakob/Postico/issues/142", "body": "I've run into an issue where one could potentially have unexpected data loss when working with temp tables. While it is perfectly logical, that some state could be lost,it can be unexpected. Disconnection on idle makes sense most of the time, but maybe there is a way for you to check if temp tables exist before cutting the connection.

Something similar probably is true for `SET` and especially for `SET search_path`, which might lead to a query unexpectedly failing after the user has been inactive. Maybe there is a way to save this state before disconnecting and re-establishing the connection with the same configuration.
